This paper is about natural language processing (NLP) and neural networks, which are commonly studied in the computer science subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of deep learning techniques, which are often studied in the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper focuses on the development of a new model for sentiment analysis, which is a common task in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of recurrent and convolutional neural networks also suggests that the paper may be relevant to the subfields of neural networks (cs.NE) and computer vision (cs.CV).
